Here is the cleaned-up text:

OmniOut for OmniScripts and FlexCards allows you to run LWCs off-platform on third-party websites. Display OmniScripts and FlexCards and connect to Salesforce from a content management system's (CMS) external website.

Required Versions:
- OmniOut for OmniScripts: Vlocity Insurance and Health Summer '20, CME Summer '20
- OmniOut for FlexCards: Summer '21

Before You Begin:

- Ensure you have a Content Management System built.
- Install Node and npm. Use Node version 14 with OmniOut.
- Download Visual Studio Code.
- Download the OmniOut static resource from Salesforce.

To Add an OmniScript or FlexCard to OmniOut:

- Download your component.
- Open it in Visual Studio Code.
- Install dependencies for the OmniOut project.
- (Optional) Add any nested custom LWCs that exist in your OmniScript.
- To enable a Salesforce API connection, create a Connected App.

To Run and Deploy OmniOut:

- View and test your component by running OmniOut in development mode.
- Deploy your OmniOut application to Adobe Experience Manager or other CMS.
- (Optional) Control where your component directs users using the Navigate Action.
- Build a connection in your application.
title: Running OmniScripts and FlexCards off-Platform
